"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Analog (`@analogjs/platform`) is a fullstack Angular meta-framework built on Vite + Nitro — same server layer as Nuxt. It should be a class `c` framework preset.\n\n## Proposed changes\n\n**Detection** — add to `FRAMEWORK_PACKAGES`:\n```js\n\"@analogjs/platform\": { name: \"analog\", class: \"c\" }\n```\n\n**Preset** — add to `FRAMEWORK_PRESETS`:\n```js\nanalog: {\n  buildCommand: \"vite build\",\n  workerDir: \"dist/analog/server\",\n  workerMain: \"index.mjs\",\n  assetsDir: \"dist/client\",\n  hashedAssetsPrefix: \"assets\"\n}\n```\n\n## Why this works\n\nAnalog uses Nitro with `cloudflare-module`. Default build output:\n- `dist/analog/server/index.mjs` — Worker entry + chunks\n- `dist/client/` — static assets (Vite client build)\n\nClass `c` returns the lightweight `voidPlugin()` set (wrangler sync, client stubs, drizzle, migrations) without `@cloudflare/vite-plugin`, which would conflict with Analog's Nitro build.\n\n## Tested\n\nPatched locally and deployed with `voidPlugin()` enabled — build, SSR, and static assets all working.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/void-sdk/void/issues/4/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/void-sdk/void/issues/4/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911/events","html_url":"https://github.com/withastro/astro/issues/15911","id":4074277184,"node_id":"I_kwDOFL76Q87y2IlA","number":15911,"title":"Astro v6 regression: define globals are shared between prerendering and client builds, leading to failed hydration","user":{"login":"eblocha","id":55192399,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1MTkyMzk5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/55192399?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha","html_url":"https://github.com/eblocha","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/eblocha/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":3559102393,"node_id":"LA_kwDOFL76Q87UI5e5","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/labels/pkg:%20integration","name":"pkg: integration","color":"b4a8d1","default":false,"description":"Related to any renderer integration (scope)"},{"id":3559105225,"node_id":"LA_kwDOFL76Q87UI6LJ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/labels/pkg:%20astro","name":"pkg: astro","color":"b4a8d1","default":false,"description":"Related to the core `astro` package (scope)"},{"id":4117972130,"node_id":"LA_kwDOFL76Q871c0Si","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/labels/-%20P4:%20important","name":"- P4: important","color":"f77d4c","default":false,"description":"Violate documented behavior or significantly impacts performance (priority)"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-03-14T01:47:08Z","updated_at":"2026-05-01T15:37:01Z","closed_at":"2026-05-01T15:37:01Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Astro Info\n\n```block\nAstro                    v6.0.4\nVite                     v7.3.1\nNode                     v24.13.0\nSystem                   Linux (x64)\nPackage Manager          npm\nOutput                   static\nAdapter                  none\nIntegrations             @astrojs/starlight (v0.38.1)\n                         @analogjs/astro-angular (v2.3.0)\n```\n\n### If this issue only occurs in one browser, which browser is a problem?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the Bug\n\nI'm not entirely sure if this is an astro issue, or an issue that the integration needs to address, but I think it may be a bit of both.\n\nI am using `@analogjs/astro-angular` to render and hydrate Angular components in an astro app.\n\nWhen building server/prerender chunks, the `ngServerMode` variable is set to `true` by the `@analogjs/astro-angular` integration as a vite [`define`](https://vite.dev/config/shared-options#define) global. This global is used inside places like `@angular/core` to perform additional checks or different code paths for the server only. It sets this variable when the `build.ssr` vite option is truthy.\n\nIn Astro v5, a separate vite configuration was created for client and prerendering phases. In the client phase, `ssr` was not set to true, so the integration did not set this global.\n\nHowever, since the client build step re-uses the same vite builder as the prerender step, this `define` variable _is still set to true_ when building the client.\n\nThis causes issues during hydration, eventually leading to an exception: https://github.com/analogjs/analog/issues/2112\n\nI think the integration may need some way to configure `define` globals for the client environment only: https://github.com/withastro/astro/blob/main/packages/astro/src/core/build/static-build.ts#L408\n\n### What's the expected result?\n\n`define` variables set for prerendering should not leak to the client build. The server and client phases should be more isolated.\n\n### Link to Minimal Reproducible Example\n\nhttps://github.com/eblocha/astro-angular-experiments/tree/astro-6-vite-7\n\n### Participation\n\n- [ ] I am willing to submit a pull request for this issue.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/withastro/astro/issues/15911/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2332","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2332/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2332/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2332/events","html_url":"https://github.com/analogjs/analog/issues/2332","id":4382412737,"node_id":"I_kwDOHnhHGM8AAAABBTZPwQ","number":2332,"title":"Sourcemap out of sync with the actual code when testing","user":{"login":"Bricklou","id":15181236,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTgxMjM2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/15181236?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bricklou","html_url":"https://github.com/Bricklou","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bricklou/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bricklou/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Bricklou/gists{/gist_id}"