users/kSherp/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kSherp/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kSherp/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Please provide the environment you discovered this bug in.\n\n```text\n@angular/core                          21.2.8\n@angular/common                        21.2.8\n@angular/compiler                      21.2.8\n@angular/compiler-cli                  21.2.8\n@angular/platform-browser              21.2.8\n@angular/platform-browser-dynamic      21.2.8\n@angular/build                         21.2.7\n@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular          2.4.5\n@analogjs/vitest-angular               2.4.5\nvite                                   7.3.2\nvitest                                 4.1.4\n@vitest/browser                        4.1.4\n@vitest/browser-playwright             4.1.4\nnode                                   22\n```\n\nReproduced on:\n- Windows 11 (host)\n- Linux (Docker, mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.59.1-noble)\n\n### Which area/package is the issue in?\n\nvite-plugin-angular\n\n### Description\n\nAfter upgrading `@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular` and `@analogjs/vitest-angular` from `2.3.1` to `2.4.5`, browser tests for Angular components that declare an **external** `styleUrl` to a `.scss` file fail during module load.\n\nUnit tests for the same components under `happy-dom` (Vitest node path) pass with the same plugin configuration. Only the Vitest browser module-runner path is affected. Also tests do not fail if the component uses inline `styles: [...]` instead of an external `styleUrl` pointing to `.scss`. So the regression appears to be specific to the external style resource path rather than browser mode in general.\n\n### Minimal reproduction\n\n[Github Repo](https://github.com/kSherp/analog-repro)\n\nA standalone project outside of any monorepo reproduces the bug. Validated results:\n\n- fails on Windows 11 with `@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular@2.4.5`\n- fails on Linux (Docker, `mcr.microsoft.com/playwright:v1.59.1-noble`) with\n  `@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular@2.4.5`\n- passes on Windows 11 after downgrading only\n  `@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular` / `@analogjs/vitest-angular` to `2.3.1`\n- passes on Linux after the same downgrade\n\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\n\n```true\n21:34:25 [vite] (client) Pre-transform error: [sass] expected \"{\".\n  ╷\n1 │ export default \":host {\\n  color: red;\\n}\"\n  │                                           ^\n  ╵\n  src\\foo.component.scss 1:43  root stylesheet\n  Plugin: vite:css\n  File: .../analog-repro/src/foo.component.scss?analog-inline:1:43\n  [sass] expected \"{\".\n    ╷\n  1 │ export default \":host {\\n  color: red;\\n}\"\n    │                                           ^\n    ╵\n    src\\foo.component.scss 1:43  root stylesheet\n ❯  chromium  src/foo.component.browser.spec.ts (0 test)\n\n⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯ Failed Suites 1 ⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯\n\n FAIL   chromium  src/foo.component.browser.spec.ts [ src/foo.component.browser.spec.ts ]\nError: Failed to import test file .../analog-repro/src/foo.component.browser.spec.ts\nCaused by: TypeError: Failed to fetch dynamically imported module: .../analog-repro/src/foo.component.browser.spec.ts?import&browserv=1775932464917\n⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯⎯[1/1]⎯\n```\n\n### Other information\n\nThe `load` hook for `?analog-inline` reads the source, runs it through `preprocessCSS`, and returns a JavaScript module (`export default \"<compiled css>\"`). The resolved id at that point still ends in `.scss?analog-inline`, so Vite's `vite:css` matches it by extension via `cssLangRE` and runs its own `transform` on the module, handing the already-compiled JavaScript payload to Sass.\n\n`2.3.1` rewrote external `styleUrl`s to `?inline` (not `?analog-inline`) and let Vite's native inline CSS handling own the module end-to-end, so no double processing occurred. The switch to `?analog-inline` appears to have been introduced in the 2.4.x line to work around Vite's `?raw` / `?inline` security checks. However, the rewritten id still keeps the `.scss` extension, which allows `vite:css` to match it again.\n\nOne direction that closed the symptom for us locally: route the compiled inline style through a virtual module id without a stylesheet extension. With a `\\0virtual:`-style id, `cssLangRE` no longer matches and `vite:css` does not re-enter, while the `load` hook still returns the same `export default \"<compiled css>\"` payload the JIT runtime expects. Applying this shape to our local `node_modules/@analogjs/vite-plugin-angular` made the monorepo's browser test suite pass on Windows. There may be a simpler or more idiomatic fix on your side — sharing this only as one working approach.\n\n### I would be willing to submit a PR to fix this issue\n\n- [x] Yes\n- [ ] No","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2280/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2280/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2092","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/analogjs/analog/issues/2092/labels{/name}","comments_