land, e.g.:\n\n```astro\n<TestComponent client:load />\n```\n\n4. Open the page in dev and inspect HTML.\n\n## Actual behavior\n\nThe page includes both:\n\n- scoped Angular style (correct), for example:\n\n```html\n<style ng-app-id=\"ng\">p[_ngcontent-ng-c2390725685] { color: red; }</style>\n```\n\n- and unscoped Vite style (incorrect):\n\n```html\n<style data-vite-dev-id=\"/home/.../src/components/app/test.component.scss\">p { color: red; }</style>\n<script type=\"module\" src=\"/src/components/app/test.component.scss\"></script>\n```\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nOnly the Angular-scoped/encapsulated component style should be applied; no unscoped duplicate stylesheet should be injected.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n### Which area/package is the issue in?\n\nastro-angular\n\n### Description\n\n## Summary\n\nWhen using `@analogjs/astro-angular` with component `styleUrl`/`styleUrls`, the same stylesheet is loaded twice in dev:\n\n- once correctly scoped/encapsulated by Angular,\n- once as an unscoped Vite-injected stylesheet (`data-vite-dev-id`).\n\nThis causes global style leakage and duplicates CSS work.\n\n## Related historical issue\n\nThis appears similar to previously fixed issue:\n\n- #142\n- fixed by https://github.com/analogjs/analog/pull/167\n\nIt looks like a regression in the current pipeline.\n\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\n\n```true\n\n```\n\n### Other information\n\n## Notes / hypothesis\n\nCurrent `vite-plugin-angular` behavior appears to allow an extra direct stylesheet request in dev for component style files, which then gets injected by Vite as global CSS.\n\nPotentially relevant implementation details in current plugin:\n\n- `enableResourceInlining: false` is forced for Angular compiler read configuration,\n- `externalRuntimeStyles` is only enabled with `liveReload`,\n- a separate non-`ngcomp` path still allows Vite to inject the stylesheet directly.\n\n### I would be willing to submit a PR to fix this issue\n\n- [ ] Yes\n- [ ] No","reactions":