njectContent<PostAttributes>('slug').pipe(\r\n    tap((x) => console.log(x))\r\n  );\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe console output is:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0c0e65d0-7fee-489b-accb-b2b20b5641af)\r\n\r\nThere is almost no resources on how to use .agx content files but from what I understand it should work exactly like .md content files without the need to adjust the `injectContent` or anything else in the code.\r\n\r\nThe behavior is the same regardless of the .agx file's content.\r\n\r\n### Please provide the exception or error you saw\r\n\r\n```true\r\ncore.mjs:6467 ERROR \r\nTypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'coverImage')\r\n    at HomeComponent_Conditional_0_Template ([slug].page.ts:15:32)\r\n    at executeTemplate (core.mjs:11264:5)\r\n    at refreshView (core.mjs:12817:7)\r\n    at detectChangesInView (core.mjs:13025:5)\r\n    at detectChangesInViewIfAttached (core.mjs:12987:3)\r\n    at detectChangesInEmbeddedViews (core.mjs:12947:7)\r\n    at refreshView (core.mjs:12844:5)\r\n    at detectChangesInView (core.mjs:13025:5)\r\n    at detectChangesInViewIfAttached (core.mjs:12987:3)\r\n    at detectChangesInComponent (core.mjs:12976:3)\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n### Other information\r\n\r\nThe only resources about .agx files I found:\r\n- [What happened to Analog's experimental \".ng\" format?](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=15vHXCMhl6U) (Joshua's video)\r\n- https://github.com/analogjs/analog/pull/1012 (the original PR)\r\n- https://github.com/analogjs/analog/tree/61b1ea63fffc6eb6510cb1006922a92af9f0f3bb/apps/ng-app (an example app which has a single .agx file but uses .analog format for all pages and components which does not apply to Analog's default blog app)\r\n\r\nThat's about it, there's very little information about this feature and the official docs do not mention it at all.\r\n\r\n### I would be willing to submit a PR to fix this issue\r\n\r\n- [ ] Yes\r\n- [ ] No","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/a